      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Session 9: Mini-Project Sprint\n",
        "## Build Your First Multi-Tool Travel Planner Agent\n",
        "\n",
        "**What you'll build today:**\n",
        "- Custom tools using the `@tool` decorator\n",
        "- A single agent that uses multiple tools\n",
        "- A manager/worker multi-agent system\n",
        "- (Optional) Connect to real weather API\n",
        "\n",
        "**Duration:** 3 hours | **Level:** Beginner\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's build a travel planner that acts as your personal trip assistant!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 1: Setup & Imports\n",
        "\n",
        "First, let's install everything we need and set up our LLM."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Install required packages\n",
        "# Uncomment the line below if running for the first time\n",
        "# !pip install langchain-core langchain-google-genai langgraph requests -q\n",
        "\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import requests\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set your Google API key here\n",
        "os.environ[\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\"] = \"your-api-key-here\"\n",
        "\n",
        "from langchain_google_genai import ChatGoogleGenerativeAI\n",
        "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
        "from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize our LLM\n",
        "llm = ChatGoogleGenerativeAI(model=\"gemini-2.5-flash\", temperature=0)\n",
        "print(\"✅ Setup complete!\")\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Using model: gemini-2.5-flash\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 2: Understanding Tools\n",
        "\n",
        "**What are tools?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Tools are functions that an AI agent can call. They extend the agent's capabilities beyond just generating text.\n",
        "\n",
        "The `@tool` decorator is the simplest way to create a tool:\n",
        "- Add `@tool` above your function\n",
        "- Write a clear docstring (the agent reads this!)\n",
        "- Use simple parameter types (str, int, float)\n",
        "- Return a string result\n",
        "\n",
        "That's it! The LLM will learn to call these functions when they're helpful."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 3: Create Your First Tool - Weather\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's start simple with mock data. This tool checks the weather in a city."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "@tool\n",
        "def get_weather(city: str) -> str:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Get current weather for a city. Returns temperature and conditions.\"\"\"\n",
        "    weather_data = {\n",
        "        \"Mumbai\": \"32°C, Humid, Partly Cloudy\",\n",
        "        \"Delhi\": \"28°C, Clear Sky\",\n",
        "        \"Goa\": \"30°C, Sunny, Light Breeze\",\n",
        "        \"Paris\": \"18°C, Overcast\",\n",
        "        \"Tokyo\": \"22°C, Clear, Windy\",\n",
        "        \"London\": \"15°C, Rainy\",\n",
        "        \"New York\": \"20°C, Clear\",\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return weather_data.get(city, f\"Weather for {city}: 25°C, Pleasant\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test it directly\n",
        "print(\"Testing get_weather tool:\")\n",
        "print(get_weather.invoke(\"Mumbai\"))\n",
        "print(get_weather.invoke(\"London\"))\n",
        "print(get_weather.invoke(\"Bangkok\"))  # Unknown city"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 4: Create More Tools\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's build tools for flights, hotels, and currency conversion. All simple mock data for now."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "@tool\n",
        "def search_flights(origin: str, destination: str) -> str:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Search for flights between two cities. Returns available options with prices.\"\"\"\n",
        "    return f\"\"\"Found 3 flights from {origin} to {destination}:\n",
        "1. Morning flight - ₹4,500 (6:00 AM, 2h 15m)\n",
        "2. Afternoon flight - ₹5,200 (1:30 PM, 2h 30m)\n",
        "3. Evening flight - ₹3,800 (8:00 PM, 2h 45m)\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "@tool\n",
        "def search_hotels(city: str, budget: str) -> str:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Search hotels in a city within a budget range. Budget can be: budget, mid, or luxury.\"\"\"\n",
        "    hotels = {\n",
        "        \"budget\": f\"\"\"Hotels in {city} (Budget):\n",
        "1. Backpacker Inn - ₹800/night (Rating: 3.5/5)\n",
        "2. City Lodge - ₹1,200/night (Rating: 3.8/5)\"\"\",\n",
        "        \"mid\": f\"\"\"Hotels in {city} (Mid-range):\n",
        "1. Comfort Suites - ₹3,500/night (Rating: 4.2/5)\n",
        "2. Garden Hotel - ₹4,000/night (Rating: 4.0/5)\"\"\",\n",
        "        \"luxury\": f\"\"\"Hotels in {city} (Luxury):\n",
        "1. Grand Palace - ₹12,000/night (Rating: 4.8/5)\n",
        "2. Royal Taj - ₹15,000/night (Rating: 4.9/5)\"\"\",\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return hotels.get(budget.lower(), hotels[\"mid\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "@tool\n",
        "def convert_currency(amount: float, from_currency: str, to_currency: str) -> str:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Convert between currencies. Supports: INR, USD, EUR, JPY, GBP.\"\"\"\n",
        "    rates = {\"INR\": 1, \"USD\": 0.012, \"EUR\": 0.011, \"JPY\": 1.79, \"GBP\": 0.0095}\n",
        "    if from_currency not in rates or to_currency not in rates:\n",
        "        return f\"Sorry, I don't have rates for {from_currency} or {to_currency}\"\n",
        "    inr_amount = amount / rates.get(from_currency, 1)\n",
        "    converted = inr_amount * rates.get(to_currency, 1)\n",
        "    return f\"{amount} {from_currency} = {converted:.2f} {to_currency}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test each tool\n",
        "print(\"\\n=== Testing search_flights ===\")\n",
        "print(search_flights.invoke({\"origin\": \"Mumbai\", \"destination\": \"Goa\"}))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n=== Testing search_hotels ===\")\n",
        "print(search_hotels.invoke({\"city\": \"Goa\", \"budget\": \"mid\"}))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n=== Testing convert_currency ===\")\n",
        "print(convert_currency.invoke({\"amount\": 5000, \"from_currency\": \"INR\", \"to_currency\": \"USD\"}))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 5: Build Your First Agent\n",
        "\n",
        "**What is an agent?**\n",
        "\n",
        "An agent = LLM + Tools + Reasoning Loop\n",
        "\n",
        "The LLM decides:\n",
        "1. **Which** tools to call (based on the user's question)\n",
        "2. **When** to call them (in what order)\n",
        "3. **What parameters** to use (extracted from the query)\n",
        "4. **When to stop** and give the final answer\n",
        "\n",
        "We use `create_react_agent` which implements the ReAct (Reasoning + Acting) pattern."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Combine all tools\n",
        "tools = [get_weather, search_flights, search_hotels, convert_currency]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the agent\n",
        "travel_agent = create_react_agent(\n",
        "    model=llm,\n",
        "    tools=tools,\n",
        "    prompt=\"\"\"You are a helpful travel planning assistant. Help users plan trips by checking weather, \n",
        "finding flights and hotels, and converting currencies. Be friendly and give practical advice. \n",
        "Always provide a clear summary at the end.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Travel agent created!\")\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Agent has access to {len(tools)} tools\")\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Tools: {', '.join([t.name for t in tools])}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 6: Test Your Agent - Simple Query\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's ask the agent a simple question about weather."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Ask the agent a simple question\n",
        "response = travel_agent.invoke(\n",
        "    {\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the weather like in Goa right now?\"}]}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print the conversation\n",
        "print(\"=== Agent Conversation ===\")\n",
        "for msg in response[\"messages\"]:\n",
        "    role = msg.type if hasattr(msg, 'type') else 'unknown'\n",
        "    content = msg.content if hasattr(msg, 'content') else str(msg)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if \"tool_calls\" in str(msg) or \"[\" in str(content[:50]):\n",
        "        print(f\"\\n🔧 {role}: [Tool call]\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"\\n🤖 {role}: {content[:300]}\")\n",
        "        if len(content) > 300:\n",
        "            print(\"...\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 7: Test Your Agent - Complex Query\n",
        "\n",
        "Now let's ask a complex question that requires multiple tools!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Ask a complex question\n",
        "response = travel_agent.invoke(\n",
        "    {\"messages\": [{\n",
        "        \"role\": \"user\",\n",
        "        \"content\": \"\"\"I want to plan a trip from Mumbai to Goa. \n",
        "What's the weather there? \n",
        "Find me a mid-range hotel and the cheapest flight. \n",
        "Also, how much is ₹10,000 in USD?\"\"\"\n",
        "    }]}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print just the final answer\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"🤖 AGENT'S FINAL ANSWER:\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "final_message = response[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
        "print(final_message.content)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 8: Understanding the Manager/Worker Pattern\n",
        "\n",
        "**Single Agent vs Manager/Worker:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Single Agent:** One LLM with ALL tools. Good for simple scenarios.\n",
        "- **Manager/Worker:** Specialized agents (workers) that each handle specific tasks. A manager decides who handles what.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why use Manager/Worker?**\n",
        "- Each worker is focused (better at their job)\n",
        "- Scales better (easy to add new specialists)\n",
        "- Better control (manager decides routing)\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "         ┌──────────┐\n",
        "         │ Manager  │\n",
        "         │ (Router) │\n",
        "         └────┬─────┘\n",
        "              │\n",
        "    ┌─────────┼─────────┐\n",
        "    ▼         ▼         ▼\n",
        " ┌────────┐┌────────┐┌────────┐\n",
        " │Weather ││ Flight ││ Hotel  │\n",
        " │Worker  ││Worker  ││Worker  │\n",
        " └────────┘└────────┘└────────┘\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 9: Create Specialist Worker Agents\n",
        "\n",
        "Each worker focuses on one area of expertise."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Worker 1: Weather specialist\n",
        "weather_worker = create_react_agent(\n",
        "    model=llm,\n",
        "    tools=[get_weather],\n",
        "    prompt=\"\"\"You are a weather specialist. Provide detailed weather information \n",
        "and practical packing advice based on the weather conditions.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Worker 2: Flight specialist\n",
        "flight_worker = create_react_agent(\n",
        "    model=llm,\n",
        "    tools=[search_flights, convert_currency],\n",
        "    prompt=\"\"\"You are a flight booking specialist. Find the best flights and help \n",
        "with currency conversion for prices. Give clear recommendations.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Worker 3: Hotel specialist\n",
        "hotel_worker = create_react_agent(\n",
        "    model=llm,\n",
        "    tools=[search_hotels, convert_currency],\n",
        "    prompt=\"\"\"You are a hotel booking specialist. Find the best hotels based on budget \n",
        "and help with currency conversion. Recommend good value options.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Created 3 specialist workers:\")\n",
        "print(\"   - Weather Worker (expertise: weather info, packing advice)\")\n",
        "print(\"   - Flight Worker (expertise: flight search, currency conversion)\")\n",
        "print(\"   - Hotel Worker (expertise: hotel search, budget planning)\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 10: Build the Manager Function\n",
        "\n",
        "The manager is a simple Python function that:\n",
        "1. Classifies the user's query (what topics are mentioned?)\n",
        "2. Routes to the appropriate workers\n",
        "3. Combines the results into a helpful answer"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def travel_manager(user_query: str) -> dict:\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Manager function that routes queries to specialist workers.\n",
        "    \n",
        "    Steps:\n",
        "    1. Classify the query using the LLM\n",
        "    2. Route to appropriate workers\n",
        "    3. Combine and summarize results\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Step 1: Ask LLM to classify the query\n",
        "    routing_prompt = f\"\"\"Classify this travel query into categories.\n",
        "Reply with ONLY the category names, comma-separated. Use lowercase.\n",
        "Categories: weather, flights, hotels\n",
        "\n",
        "Query: {user_query}\n",
        "\n",
        "Categories:\"\"\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    route_response = llm.invoke(routing_prompt)\n",
        "    categories = route_response.content.lower()\n",
        "    print(f\"📊 Classified query into: {categories}\")\n",
        "    \n",
        "    results = {}\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Step 2: Route to appropriate workers\n",
        "    if \"weather\" in categories:\n",
        "        print(\"📡 Routing to Weather Worker...\")\n",
        "        resp = weather_worker.invoke(\n",
        "            {\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_query}]}\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        results[\"weather\"] = resp[\"messages\"][-1].content\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if \"flight\" in categories:\n",
        "        print(\"✈️  Routing to Flight Worker...\")\n",
        "        resp = flight_worker.invoke(\n",
        "            {\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_query}]}\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        results[\"flights\"] = resp[\"messages\"][-1].content\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if \"hotel\" in categories:\n",
        "        print(\"🏨 Routing to Hotel Worker...\")\n",
        "        resp = hotel_worker.invoke(\n",
        "            {\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_query}]}\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        results[\"hotels\"] = resp[\"messages\"][-1].content\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Step 3: Combine results\n",
        "    combined = \"\\n\\n\".join(\n",
        "        [f\"**{k.title()}:**\\n{v}\" for k, v in results.items()]\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Step 4: Final summary from LLM\n",
        "    summary_prompt = f\"\"\"Based on the following travel research, provide a helpful travel plan.\n",
        "    \n",
        "User's question: {user_query}\n",
        "\n",
        "Research results:\n",
        "{combined}\n",
        "\n",
        "Provide a friendly, organized travel plan summary:\"\"\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    final = llm.invoke(summary_prompt)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"categories\": categories,\n",
        "        \"results\": results,\n",
        "        \"summary\": final.content\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✅ Manager function created!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 11: Test the Manager/Worker System\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's ask the manager a complex question and see how it routes to workers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Test the manager with a multi-category query\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"TESTING MANAGER/WORKER SYSTEM\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "\n",
        "result = travel_manager(\n",
        "    \"\"\"I'm planning a trip from Delhi to Goa next week. \n",
        "What's the weather there? \n",
        "Find me a budget hotel and the cheapest flight.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"🗺️  TRAVEL PLAN SUMMARY:\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(result[\"summary\"])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 12: Real Weather Data (Optional)\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's connect to a real API! Open-Meteo provides free weather data with no API key required.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is optional - you can skip if internet is limited."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "@tool\n",
        "def get_real_weather(city: str) -> str:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Get REAL current weather using Open-Meteo API (free, no API key needed).\"\"\"\n",
        "    # City coordinates\n",
        "    coords = {\n",
        "        \"Mumbai\": (19.08, 72.88),\n",
        "        \"Delhi\": (28.61, 77.23),\n",
        "        \"Goa\": (15.50, 73.83),\n",
        "        \"Bangalore\": (12.97, 77.59),\n",
        "        \"Paris\": (48.86, 2.35),\n",
        "        \"Tokyo\": (35.68, 139.69),\n",
        "        \"New York\": (40.71, -74.01),\n",
        "        \"London\": (51.51, -0.13),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    \n",
        "    if city not in coords:\n",
        "        return f\"Sorry, I don't have coordinates for {city}. Available: {', '.join(list(coords.keys())[:5])}...\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    lat, lon = coords[city]\n",
        "    url = f\"https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude={lat}&longitude={lon}&current_weather=true\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        resp = requests.get(url, timeout=5)\n",
        "        if resp.status_code == 200:\n",
        "            data = resp.json()[\"current_weather\"]\n",
        "            temp = data[\"temperature\"]\n",
        "            wind = data[\"windspeed\"]\n",
        "            return f\"Weather in {city}: {temp}°C, Wind: {wind} km/h\"\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            return f\"Could not fetch weather for {city}: API error\"\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        return f\"Could not fetch weather for {city}: {type(e).__name__}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test with real data\n",
        "print(\"Testing real weather API:\")\n",
        "print(get_real_weather.invoke(\"Mumbai\"))\n",
        "print(get_real_weather.invoke(\"London\"))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 13: Upgrade Agent with Real Weather\n",
        "\n",
        "Replace the mock weather tool with the real one!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Create tools list with real weather\n",
        "upgraded_tools = [get_real_weather, search_flights, search_hotels, convert_currency]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create upgraded agent\n",
        "upgraded_agent = create_react_agent(\n",
        "    model=llm,\n",
        "    tools=upgraded_tools,\n",
        "    prompt=\"\"\"You are a helpful travel planning assistant with access to real-time weather data. \n",
        "Help users plan trips by checking actual weather, finding flights and hotels, and converting currencies.\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test with real weather\n",
        "response = upgraded_agent.invoke(\n",
        "    {\"messages\": [{\n",
        "        \"role\": \"user\",\n",
        "        \"content\": \"What's the actual weather in Tokyo right now? Should I pack warm clothes?\"\n",
        "    }]}\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(\"🤖 UPGRADED AGENT RESPONSE (with real weather):\")\n",
        "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
        "print(response[\"messages\"][-1].content)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part 14: Key Takeaways\n",
        "\n",
        "**What you learned:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Tools** - Functions that agents can call to extend their capabilities\n",
        "   - Use `@tool` decorator\n",
        "   - Write clear docstrings\n",
        "   - Use simple parameters and return strings\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Single Agent** - One LLM with multiple tools\n",
        "   - Good for simple cases\n",
        "   - LLM decides which tools to call\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Manager/Worker Pattern** - Specialized agents\n",
        "   - Manager routes queries to specialists\n",
        "   - Workers are focused on their domain\n",
        "   - Scales well for complex applications\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Real APIs** - Connect to live data\n",
        "   - Open-Meteo for weather (free, no key)\n",
        "   - Easy to add, error handling important\n",
        "\n",
        "**What's next:**\n",
        "- Add restaurant search tool\n",
        "- Build an activities worker\n",
        "- Connect more real APIs\n",
        "- Deploy as a web app or chatbot!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Exercises\n",
        "\n",
        "Try these on your own!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
